1
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:14,480
Prepare for obliteration,
earthling scum.

2
00:00:14,560 --> 00:00:17,280
Actually, Mr Strax, if you could just
take him aside for a moment,

3
00:00:17,360 --> 00:00:19,360
I have some officers on the way.

4
00:00:19,440 --> 00:00:22,360
As you wish. Human filth.

5
00:00:23,240 --> 00:00:25,200
Sorry. He's new.

6
00:00:25,520 --> 00:00:28,120
Funny-looking fellow. Turkish, is he?

7
00:00:28,840 --> 00:00:32,320
He is a genetically modified
clone warrior from outer space.

8
00:00:32,640 --> 00:00:34,840
Ah. Makes sense. (CHUCKLES)

9
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:37,400
Well, what a case.

10
00:00:37,480 --> 00:00:40,600
Identical twins,
poison undetectable to science,

11
00:00:40,720 --> 00:00:42,480
an ancient Egyptian curse...

12
00:00:42,640 --> 00:00:45,800
Once more Scotland Yard is in your debt,
Madame Vastra.

13
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:47,200
Where would we be without you?

14
00:00:47,280 --> 00:00:49,440
Mmm. Quite some distance from a clue,
one imagines.

15
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:52,440
Yeah, you might be right. Yeah...

16
00:00:53,840 --> 00:00:55,880
Does it ever hurt?

17
00:00:56,440 --> 00:00:58,000
Does what hurt?

18
00:00:58,080 --> 00:01:00,960
Well, your skin condition.
Always wondered.

19
00:01:01,560 --> 00:01:03,320
It's not a condition, Inspector.

20
00:01:03,480 --> 00:01:05,240
-It's just skin.
-Are you sure?

21
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:07,960
I am, as I may have failed to mention,

22
00:01:08,080 --> 00:01:11,000
an intelligent reptile
from an ancient civilisation

23
00:01:11,080 --> 00:01:12,640
long preceding mankind.

24
00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:15,640
Many of us slumber
under the Earth's crust.

25
00:01:15,880 --> 00:01:19,320
Madame was accidentally awoken by
an extension to the London Underground.

26
00:01:19,520 --> 00:01:21,440
Well, that would account for it.

27
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:24,400
I was not initially keen
on the society of apes.

28
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:27,000
But I made the most
elementary of errors.

29
00:01:27,640 --> 00:01:29,800
-I fell in love.
-What, with the Turkish fellow?

30
00:01:29,960 --> 00:01:32,880
No. Not with the Turkish fellow.

31
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:38,480
Good Lord. Good Lord.

32
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:41,800
-Well, come along, my dear.
-Yes, my darling.

33
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:45,120
-Good Lord.
-(BOTH GIGGLING)

34
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:48,720
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

35
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:50,680
(BOTH SIGH)

36
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:53,680
Still no word from The Doctor, then?

37
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:55,360
-No, my dear.
-(SIGHS)

38
00:01:55,440 --> 00:01:56,840
And there won't be.

39
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:58,920
He can't sulk in his box forever.

40
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:00,200
(SIGHS)

41
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:04,280
A heartbreak is a burden to us all.
Pity the man with two.

42
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:10,760
It's starting to snow.

43
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:12,320
But it can't be.

44
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:14,240
Well, it is nearly Christmas.

45
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:16,160
-But the clouds.
-What about them?

46
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:17,840
There aren't any.

